1 - alarm button

3 - button 1

Y - action:

3 - long click

children.description:
1 - Device turned OFF

children.name: Amber Alert state
children.description:
0 - Turned Off
1 - Turned On, count down timer started
2 - Amber Alert On button pressed to restard active timer
3 - Alarm
4 - Amber Alert turned On when timer is set to 0 seconds

children.description: Sends Amber Alert time-out configured value

children.name: Heart Rate Alert
children.description: Sends heart rate (BPM) from Xiaomi Mi Band 2

children.name: Beacon ID's
children.description:
Data structure:

Data part: 1 Byte
Beacon flag: 1 Byte
Beacon ID (iBeacon/Eddystone): 20 Bytes/16 Bytes
Signal strength: 1 Byte

children.name: Bluetooth Home Zone
children.description:
Bits describe the causes of violations:
0 - None
1 - Movement (Only for Ela MOV sensor)
2 - RSSI threshold violation
4 - BLE missing

children.name: Proximity Violation state
children.description:
Bits describe the causes of violations:
1 - RSSI threshold violation
0 - End of RSSI violation

children.name: Proximity violation source 1
children.description:
Proximity violation source with Teltonika devices

MAC address which violates personal space
Example of encoded HEX ASCII text:
HEX: 44 35 41 34 31 42 38 42 31 30 37 35
HEX ASCII to text: D5A41B8B1075
(NOTE! From firmware version Rev.329 device sends IMEI instead of MAC address)
Example:
HEX -> ASCII (String)
3031343731353942383241454643 -> 0147159B82AEFC
HEX -> DEC
0147159B82AEFC -> 359633105628924

children.name: Proximity violation source 2
children.description:
Proximity violation source with iBeacons

Example of UUID encoded HEX to ASCII format:
HEX: 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 41 42 42 43 43 35 32 36 46 36 46 36 44 33 31
HEX to ASCII format: AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABBCC526F6F6D31

children.name: Proximity duration
children.description:
Violation time in seconds.
Included as an IO element with AVL ID 875

children.name: BLE MAC address
children.description:
BLE MAC address of device.
Example of encoded HEX ASCII text:
HEX: 44 35 41 34 31 42 38 42 31 30 37 35
HEX ASCII to text: D5A41B8B1075

children.name: BT Status
children.description:
0 - BT is disabled
1 - BT Enabled, not device connected
2 - Device connected, BTv3 Only
3 - Device connected, BLE only
4 - Device connected, BLE + BT

children.description:
getparam #

Returns selected parameter value.

2.# - second ID value.
3.# - third ID value.

children.name: Get params #100 and #179

getparam #;#;…

children.description:
setparam #:#

Sets selected parameter value

children.description:
setparam #:#;#:#;…

children.name: Redirects to other server
children.description:
flush #,#,#,#,#,#,#

Redirects device to other server.
1.# - IMEI.
2.# - APN.
3.# - LOGIN.
4.# - PASS.
5.# - IP.
6.# - PORT.
7.# - MODE (0-TCP/1-UDP).

children.name: Delete records
children.description: Delete all records from SD card.

children.name: Get battery
children.description: Returns battery state info.

children.name: Get 'watch dogs'
children.description: Returns all information about 'watch dogs'

children.name: Load default config
children.description: Load default configuration.

children.name: Set key
children.description:
setkey # #

Add new or change current configuration keyword. If device is locked, keyword cannot be changed.
1.# - old keyword (if adding new keyword space).
2.# - new keyword.

children.name: Delete key
children.description:
delkey #

Remove existing keyword (If device is locked, keyword cannot be changed).
1.# - old keyword.

children.name: Get black box
children.description:
bbread #

Return black box information (HEX value of event ID and HEX value of custom data field (optional)).
1.# - returns entered number of latest events. When # is omitted the latest events are packed to single SMS.

children.name: Get black box HEX
children.description:
bbinfo #

Return same information as bbread command but additional all events timestamp is written in HEX.
1.# - returns entered number of latest events. When # is omitted the latest events are packed to single SMS.

children.description:
Returns requested Bluetooth list.
# - 0,1 or 2 (0 – Discovered, 1 – Paired, 2 – Connected, 3 – Discovered BT4/BLE devices).

children.name: Scan
children.description: Starts Bluetooth scan.

children.name: Set visible 10 sec
children.description:
Sets Bluetooth to visible with TMO.
# - visibility TMO (from 1 to 255 seconds).

children.name: Disconnect
children.description:
Disconnects from current device and pauses auto connect functionality for TMO.
# - none or TMO (from 1 to 255 seconds).

children.name: Unpair
children.description:
Unpair Bluetooth device.
# - all, BT address (all – unpair all devices, BT address – unpair only specified MAC address).
Bluetooth Commands

children.name: Functional commands
Stop tracking
children.description:
Note: This command is supported from 55.00.00 firmware version.

on_demand_tracking#

Tracking on Demand functionality. # = Value ↓
0 – Stops Tracking on Demand functionality.
1 – Starts Tracking on Demand functionality.
2 – Generates one high priority record and inititates data sending to server.

children.name: Start tracking
children.description:
Note: This command is supported from 55.00.00 firmware version.

on_demand_tracking#

Tracking on Demand functionality. # = Value ↓
0 – Stops Tracking on Demand functionality.
1 – Starts Tracking on Demand functionality.
2 – Generates one high priority record and inititates data sending to server.
